-- Indonesia's Bank Central Asia posts 18 pct rise in 9-mth profit to Sept
-- By Fransiska Nangoy
-- Thu Oct 30, 2014 05:31AM EDT
-- None



JAKARTA, Oct 30 (Reuters) - Indonesia's biggest bank by market value, PT Bank Central Asia Tbk <BBCA.JK>, on Thursday reported a rise of nearly 18 percent  in net profit for the nine months ended September.

The lender posted net profit of 12.2 trillion rupiah ($1.01 billion), up 17.7 percent from the year earlier period.